N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 2105.7 - Disclosure by employees

State Regulations

It shall be unlawful for any officer or employee of the
commission, or for any official adviser or consultant to the commission, to
disclose, otherwise than in the course of official duty, any information
obtained under the Act, or to use any such information for personal
benefit. Notes
